# DLL Injection Detection Lab using Wazuh and Sysmon (MITRE ATT&CK T1055.001)

## Overview

This project demonstrates the detection of Dynamic-Link Library (DLL) Injection using Wazuh and Sysmon in a controlled lab environment.

DLL Injection is a process injection technique frequently used by malware authors to execute malicious code inside legitimate processes. This technique is mapped to MITRE ATT&CK T1055.001.

The objective of this lab is to:

* Simulate DLL Injection activity
* Monitor endpoint activity using Sysmon
* Collect Windows Event Logs with the Wazuh Agent
* Detect suspicious process injection behavior in Wazuh
* Perform alert validation and investigation

## MITRE ATT&CK Mapping

| Technique                      | ID        |
| ------------------------------ | --------- |
| Dynamic-Link Library Injection | T1055.001 |
| Process Injection              | T1055     |

## Lab Environment

### Wazuh Manager

* Operating System: Kali Linux
* Wazuh Manager Version: 4.x

### Endpoint

* Operating System: Windows 10
* Sysmon Installed
* Wazuh Agent Installed

## Attack Simulation

The DLL Injection attack was simulated using InjectProc.

Command executed:

InjectProc.exe dll_inj hello-world-x64.dll cmd.exe

Expected Result:

* DLL injected into cmd.exe
* Remote thread created
* DLL executed under target process context
* "Hello World" message displayed

## Detection Workflow

1. Install Sysmon
2. Configure Sysmon logging
3. Configure Wazuh Agent
4. Execute DLL Injection
5. Collect Sysmon Events
6. Generate Wazuh Alerts
7. Perform Threat Hunting Investigation

